 from Arduino 5V pin — servo draws too much current, use external 5V supply","Center pulse width may need trimming via potentiometer on the servo body","Not a position servo — no way to command a specific angle, only speed and direction"],"datasheet_url":""},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[[48,66]]},"smart_blocks:docs/parts/osepp-ls-955cr-continuous-rotation-servo-360-degree.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":null},"embeddings":{},"text":null,"length":0,"last_read":{"hash":"181pac","at":1776152926649},"key":"docs/parts/osepp-ls-955cr-continuous-rotation-servo-360-degree.md#---frontmatter---","lines":[1,20],"size":1005,"outlinks":[{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":3},{"title":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","target":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","line":16},{"title":"arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb","target":"arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb","line":16},{"title":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","target":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","line":16}],"class_name":"SmartBlock"},
